    <title>Photos from everywhere</title>
    <link>file://localhost/Users/arnodrucker/Documents/A%26R%20Web%20site/Ruth_and_Arnos_Pages/Photo_Albums/Pages/Shirakawa-go,_Kagaya_Onsen.html</link>
    <description>Takayama has a museum for its enormous floats which are used a few times each year in great ceremonial processions. We also visited a Folk Museum - once a farmer’s house where silkworms were cultivated in the attic. Shirakawa-go is a UNESCO Heritage village - people still live and work there. At the Kagaya Onsen we wore traditional yukatas and enjoyed the hot baths and slept on futons on the tatami floor. The staff of this enormous modern hotel bid us farewell in the rain as our bus left.</description>
